<div class="minimal-section">
  <div class="divider"></div>
  
  <div class="principle">
    <p class="principle-number">01 — Essential</p>
    <h3>Simplicity</h3>
    <p>
      Strip away the unnecessary. Every element must earn its place. Minimalism isn't about having less—it's about making room for more: more clarity, more focus, more impact. Remove until only the essence remains.
    </p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="principle">
    <p class="principle-number">02 — Fundamental</p>
    <h3>Functionality</h3>
    <p>
      Form follows function in its purest expression. Design with purpose. Each decision should serve the user's needs directly, without decoration or distraction. Beauty emerges from utility and honesty.
    </p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="principle">
    <p class="principle-number">03 — Intentional</p>
    <h3>Space</h3>
    <p>
      Negative space is not empty—it's active. It provides breathing room, creates hierarchy, and guides attention. In minimalism, what you leave out is as important as what you include. Embrace the void.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

